### Response Model Parameter

Use `response_model` to define the structure and validation of responses:

```python
from fastapi import FastAPI
from pydantic import BaseModel

app = FastAPI()

class Item(BaseModel):
    name: str
    price: float
    tax: float | None = None
    is_offer: bool = False

class ItemOut(BaseModel):
    name: str
    price_with_tax: float

@app.post("/items/", response_model=ItemOut)
async def create_item(item: Item):
    return {
        "name": item.name,
        "price_with_tax": item.price + (item.tax or 0)
    }
```

### Filtering Response Fields

Control which fields are included in responses:

```python
@app.post("/items/", response_model=Item, response_model_exclude_unset=True)
async def create_item(item: Item):
    return item
# Only includes fields that were sent in the request

@app.get("/items/", response_model=list[Item], response_model_exclude={"tax"})
async def list_items():
    return [{"name": "Item1", "price": 10.0}]
# Excludes the 'tax' field

@app.get("/items/{pk}", response_model=Item, response_model_include={"name", "price"})
async def get_item(pk: int):
    return {"name": "Item1", "price": 10.0, "tax": 1.0}
# Only includes 'name' and 'price'
```

### Response Status Codes

Set custom status codes:

```python
from fastapi import status

@app.post("/items/", status_code=status.HTTP_201_CREATED)
async def create_item(item: Item):
    return item

@app.delete("/items/{pk}", status_code=status.HTTP_204_NO_CONTENT)
async def delete_item(pk: int):
    return None
```

### Custom Response Classes

FastAPI provides several response classes:

```python
from fastapi.responses import (
    JSONResponse,
    HTMLResponse,
    PlainTextResponse,
    FileResponse,
    StreamingResponse,
    RedirectResponse
)

@app.get("/html")
async def get_html():
    return HTMLResponse("<h1>Hello</h1>", status_code=200)

@app.get("/file")
async def get_file():
    return FileResponse("report.pdf", media_type="application/pdf")

@app.get("/stream")
async def stream_data():
    async def generate():
        for i in range(10):
            yield f"data chunk {i}\n"
    return StreamingResponse(generate(), media_type="text/plain")

@app.get("/old-page")
async def redirect():
    return RedirectResponse("/new-page")
```

### JSONResponse with Custom Headers

```python
from fastapi.responses import JSONResponse

@app.get("/api/data")
async def get_data():
    content = {"message": "Hello"}
    headers = {"X-Custom-Header": "value"}
    return JSONResponse(content=content, headers=headers)
```

